# 🧠 Laravel Project Rule (.mdc)

This project uses **Laravel** with modern architecture and PSR/SOLID principles.  
The codebase is modular, layered, and follows clean structure.

## ✅ Coding Standards
- Follow PSR-12, SOLID principles
- Use service layer + repository pattern
- Keep controllers thin, delegate logic to services
- Use DTOs or array objects for request/response transformation
- Always validate input with FormRequest
- Blade components should be reusable and simple
- Livewire is used for frontend interaction

## 🔐 Auth & Security
- Laravel Breeze is used with Livewire stack
- Supports both password login and OTP-based login via mobile
- Sanctum is used for API authentication
- spatie/laravel-permission handles roles & permissions

## 💳 Features
- OTP login system integrated with SMS
- Payment gateway handled by shetabit/payment
- Telegram bot connected via php-telegram-bot/core (no Laravel bridge)
- Toast-style notifications with Livewire + Alpine

## 🧪 Testing
- Use Feature tests for endpoints
- Use mocks/fakes for external services like SMS or Telegram

## ✏️ Notes
- You can `@` reference files and paths
- You may use emoji (✅ ❌ ⚠️ 💡) for status markers
- Prefer Persian in responses, but English in code

